Defendant Zulma Dely Mercado-Rodriguez in court with attorney Danielle L. Shelton.  Defendant Zulma Dely Mercado-Rodriguez in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  

Defendant sentenced to serve 5 MONTHS in the House of Correction with CONSECUTIVE to each other; credit for 71 days as to COUNT 1 ONLY.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Submit DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge;
*  Commit no new crimes;
*  Letter of apology to JCPenney's, Macy's and Walmart;
*  Absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Participate in vocational training;
*  Attend school part time;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
Court ordered restitution set at $0.00.
